reviews.text: Wonderfully themed bar experience in Hong Kong. The extensive Mezcal and Tequila offering make this nice bar stand out in the Hong Kong scene. The service is extremely professional but at the same time not boring, and cocktails are definitely some of the best I ever tried.

The drinks here are amazing! I'm not usually a tequila or mezcal kinda guy but the cocktails here blew my mind. I particularly loved the coconut milk punch that had coconut cream in it somewhere but was clarified and just delicious goodness. Another drink that combined Mexican and Chinese inspired ingredients whose name I didn't catch was also super tasty. The bartender owner Jay Khan was very friendly and knowledgeable but didn't go on too excessively about his fantastic creations, the way some of these modern bars sometimes tend to. Definitely my favorite bar in HK, highly recommended!
Very kind server made great recommendations and shared very detailed information about mezcal and the agave plant. Very nice boss, meticulous in his work. Loved my dynasty margarita.

The staff were very informative, which was wonderful since I don't know much about tequila. It was also good as I'm afraid there wasn't much to do there other than talk to them. The staff are 5 stars, but the atmosphere is 2.
Paloma with worm salt and Coconut Milk Punch were both incredibly yummy and creative. The bartender explained the cocktails and ingredients in detail which added to a great experience.
